  "text": "EXTENDED DATA Extended Data Figure 1 . Scaling laws used to construct the model. a, The ratio of the stellar mass to the virial mass of model galaxies at the present epoch are indicated by blue circles connected by the curve. Observed estimates for disc galaxies from weak gravitational lensing measurements [CITATION_1] are plotted as green circles with 95% confidence interval. The red line demarcates the distribution area of blue galaxies based on satellite galaxy kinematics [CITATION_2] . b, Mass fraction of the cold interstellar gas to the total baryon mass (i.e., the sum of cold interstellar gas and stars) for four mass bins are indicated by lines (blue: 10.0 < log star < 10.5 , green: 10.5 < log star < 11.0 , orange: 11.0 < log star < 11.4 , and red: 11.4 < log star ). Solid and dashed lines indicate the estimated range for each mass bin based on the observation [CITATION_3] . Circles indicate the reference points used to specify the mass fraction of the interstellar gas in the model for specific values of the stellar mass and redshift by interpolation (or extrapolation) (blue: log star = 10.25, green: log star = 10.75, and red: log star = 11.4).",
